Detailed Description

Parameter class needed for registering an application to the bluetooth protocol stack. Two different types of roles can be registered - Controller and Target. Before implementing any operations one needs to register at least one of the roles.

void BtAvrcpRegisterParams::SetSupportedCategories (  UINT8  categories  )  [inline]
 

Set the supported categories. The categories shall be set via an "OR" linking of BtAvrcpCategory parameters. In case a device supports Category 1, 2 and 4 the parameter shall be set as SetSupportedCategories(BtCategory1 | BtCategory2 | BtCategory4); compare to the Bluetooth specification in order to find out which category is to be supported.
